HEADWORD: Pikeman
<hw>Pike"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pikeman</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A soldier
armed with a pike.</def> <rj><au>Knolles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A miner who works with a pick.</def>
<rj><au>Beaconsfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A keeper of a turnpike gate.</def> <rj><au>T.
Hughes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pikestaff</ent>⟦br⟧
